Detailed Description

cvmx_sriomaint::_port_0_ctl2

These registers are accessed when a local processor or an external device wishes to examine the port baudrate information. The automatic baud rate feature is not available on this device. The SUP_* and ENB_* fields are set directly by the SRIO()_STATUS_REG[SPD] bits as a reference but otherwise have no effect.

WARNING!! Writes to this register will reinitialize the SRIO link.
